<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,586,958]" box="[160,410,586,611]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
<heading box="[160,410,586,611]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,410,586,611]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="3">External morphology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,586,958]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[235,358,622,646]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, slightly produced anteriorly, median length of crown approximately 1/2 interocular width and 1/4 transocular width; anterior margin broadly rounded in dorsal view; ocelli aligned to anterior eye angles, each equidistant between adjacent anterior eye angle and median line of crown, situated at pair of slight concavities. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[390,515,760,784]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
) with width approximately equal to transocular width; with pair of concavities near anterior margin; lateral margins convergent anteriorly; posterior margin slightly concave; dorsopleural carinae complete and oblique. Fore wings (
<figureCitation box="[244,368,864,888]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
) coriaceous; membrane including all apical cells, extending forward along costal margin to basal half of wing. Hind legs with femoral setal formula 2:1:1; length of first tarsomere greater than combined length of two more distal ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1023,1221]" box="[160,285,1023,1048]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
<heading box="[160,285,1023,1048]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1023,1048]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="3">Coloration</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1023,1221]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
Ground colour of crown, anterior third of pronotum and mesonotum light green, remainder of dorsum dark green (
<figureCitation box="[547,669,1093,1117]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Crown with transverse dark brown stripe anterior to ocelli and a dark brown ark posterior to each ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[890,1012,1128,1152]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Fore wings with dark brown stripes on and beside longitudinal veins (
<figureCitation box="[824,946,1162,1186]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Face and ventral body region pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1286,1727]" box="[160,331,1286,1311]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
<heading box="[160,331,1286,1311]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,331,1286,1311]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537" reason="3">Male genitalia</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1286,1727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[265,390,1322,1346]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10B</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately produced posteriorly; dorsal margin approximately rectilinear; posteroventral margin broadly convex; apex narrowly rounded; macrosetae near apex and posteroventral margin, few along dorsal margin; slender process arising from ventral margin and extending posterodorsally as far as apex of pygofer. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[516,641,1461,1485]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10C</figureCitation>
) subtriangular, long and slender, extending posteriorly almost as far as apex of pygofer, gradually tapered towards apex; macrosetae uniseriate along outer margin. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[601,727,1530,1554]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10D</figureCitation>
) slender, without preapical lobe, not extending as far as apex of connective, extending approximately as far as basal half of subgenital plates. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[513,639,1599,1623]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10D</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped, with well-produced dorsomedian carina. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[375,498,1634,1658]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10E</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, curved ventrally, with pair of claw-like processes at apex. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[520,641,1669,1693]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1537">Figure 10E</figureCitation>
) paired, extending below shaft of aedeagus; rami thick, curved dorsally, apices blunt.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,142,444]" box="[160,359,142,167]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">
<heading box="[160,359,142,167]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,359,142,167]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" reason="3">Female genitalia</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,142,444]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">
Abdominal sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[435,557,178,202]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure 10F</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, lateral margins parallel, tapered near apex; posterior margin with concavity bearing small prominence. Valvulae II (
<figureCitation box="[167,292,247,271]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure 10G</figureCitation>
) expanded beyond basal curvature and gradually narrowing towards acute apex; ventral and dorsal margins approximately parallel; preapical prominence distinct; primary teeth inclined trapezoid on basal and median portions (
<figureCitation box="[895,1019,316,340]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure 11H</figureCitation>
), becoming triangular at apex (
<figureCitation box="[379,485,351,375]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure11I</figureCitation>
); first ones with posterior flat area, which becomes gradually smaller towards apex, where it is absent (
<figureCitation box="[669,777,386,410]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure11J</figureCitation>
); denticles on all teeth and apical portion; ventral dentate apical portion greater than dorsal one (
<figureCitation box="[891,999,420,444]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[160,225,1281,1304]" captionTargetBox="[179,1135,143,1244]" captionTargetId="figure-78@12.[178,1138,142,1250]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Scopogonalia osteiphera sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) styles and connective, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G–J) valvula II of ovipositor: (G) lateral view; (H) tooth at median portion; (I) teeth at apical portion; (J) apex. PT, primary tooth; DT, denticle; DM, dorsal margin and VM, ventral margin of dentate apical area. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–G = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206551/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure11J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,491,585]" box="[160,285,491,516]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">
<heading box="[160,285,491,516]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,491,516]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" reason="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,491,585]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">
The species epithet, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leal" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[399,471,527,551]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euxloa">
<emphasis box="[399,471,527,551]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">euxloa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from Greek: 
<emphasis box="[633,715,527,551]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">euxloos</emphasis>
, fresh and green), refers to the green colour of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
