<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,386,774,799]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" reason="3">Comparative notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,774,937]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">
The new species is very similar externally to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavichioli" authorityYear="1986" box="[677,808,809,833]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendida">
<emphasis box="[677,808,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">S. splendida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, to a certain extent, to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cavichioli" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scopogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">S. plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from these by the paraphyses rami which are thick with blunt apices (
<figureCitation box="[168,286,879,903]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure 10E</figureCitation>
) and by the female abdominal sternite VII with the posterior margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[167,288,913,937]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1097,1120]" captionTargetBox="[179,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetId="figure-182@11.[178,1138,137,1066]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Scopogonalia euxloa sp. nov. (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) male pygofer, lateral view; (C) valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; (D) style, dorsal view; (E) anal tube, aedeagus and paraphyses, lateral view; (F) female abdominal sternite VII, ventral view; (G) valvula II of ovipositor, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; D = 0.25 mm; others = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5206545" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5206545/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1538">Figure 10F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
